## RQ2: Distribution — Histogram {.smaller}

```{r}
#| fig-height: 5

ggplot(water_2023_clean, aes(x = rate)) +
  geom_histogram(aes(y = after_stat(density)),
                 bins = 50, fill = "#4575b4", color = "white", alpha = 0.85) +
  geom_density(color = "#d73027", linewidth = 1.2) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = nat_avg, linetype = "dashed",
             color = "#d73027", linewidth = 1) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = nat_med, linetype = "dotted",
             color = "#333", linewidth = 1) +
  annotate("text", x = nat_avg + 0.003, y = Inf,
           label = paste0("Mean\n", scales::percent(nat_avg, 0.01)),
           hjust = 0, vjust = 1.5, color = "#d73027", size = 4, fontface = "bold") +
  annotate("text", x = nat_med - 0.003, y = Inf,
           label = paste0("Median\n", scales::percent(nat_med, 0.01)),
           hjust = 1, vjust = 1.5, color = "#333", size = 4, fontface = "bold") +
  scale_x_continuous(labels = scales::percent_format(accuracy = 0.1),
                     breaks = seq(0, 0.6, by = 0.1)) +
  scale_y_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0.15))) +
  labs(title = "Strongly Right-Skewed Distribution",
       subtitle = paste0(scales::percent(mean(water_2023_clean$rate < 0.02), 1), 
                         " of counties below 2% · Only ", sum(water_2023_clean$rate > 0.05), 
                         " counties exceed 5%"),
       x = "Share of households lacking plumbing", y = "Density",
       caption = SOURCE_CAPTION)
```

**Key Insights:** The distribution is extremely right-skewed with 96% of counties below 2% deprivation. Mean is `r round(nat_avg/nat_med, 1)`× the median, indicating outliers dominate. Only 34 counties exceed 5%, revealing concentration in specific communities rather than diffuse national problem.

